abstract: >
  SFA-Bench is a deterministic, model-agnostic benchmark harness for preserving
  AI reasoning failures as replayable, tamper-evident historical records. It
  supports offline artifact and ledger attestation, transcript re-derivation,
  fixed-condition fixture fingerprinting, and deterministic generator-side
  policy guidance without live model, API, provider, or network calls in CI.
  The v2.0.0-alpha.2 research tranche adds lock-bound campaign execution,
  exact adapter-boundary evidence capture, crash-safe immutable lifecycle
  records, separate offline judgment, and explicitly unratified human-review
  packaging while preserving the fixed, blind, deterministic verifier boundary.
